description:
Per kx-9v7 diagnostic (docs/audits/2026-05-26-diagnostic-500.md), all 5 originally-suspected endpoints already return correct 404 for upstream-404. The ONLY residual 500 risk is unreachable upstream — ConnectException / HttpRequestTimeoutException fall to the Throwable catch-all in Application.kt and emit 500 'internal_error'. Should be 503 with Retry-After (matching ServiceUnavailableException semantics).

Single client-level fix in gateway/.../Application.kt StatusPages:
- exception<java.net.ConnectException> { ... respond(503, ...) }
- exception<io.ktor.client.network.sockets.SocketTimeoutException> { ... respond(504, ...) }
- exception<io.ktor.client.plugins.HttpRequestTimeoutException> { ... respond(504, ...) }

Tests: extend UpstreamExceptionPathDiagnosticTest with cases for unreachable upstream (no server bound to port) and slow upstream (server delays >timeout). Asserts 503/504, not 500.
